President Trump met with leaders of the National Association of Police Organizations to discuss the support for law enforcement and the current challenges they face. The president expressed his appreciation for the endorsement from the association and highlighted the need to defend the safety of all Americans. He mentioned the recent unrest in cities like Portland and Seattle, stating that the federal government had to step in to protect federal property. The president criticized the actions of radical left extremists and expressed concern about the rise in violent crime in certain Democrat-run cities. He also discussed the issue of defunding the police and expressed his support for law enforcement. The leaders of the association raised concerns about the current state of law enforcement, including the lack of support from politicians and the challenges they face in doing their job effectively. The president assured them of his support and promised to continue backing the police.